kanji_info.image_description: A trio of mischievous, colorful hair ornaments, each with a different form or style, are playfully assembled together. They are giggling and pointing at each other, each boasting about their unique shape.

kanji.koohii1: Japanese kamikaze pilots (and the American from Dr. Strangelove) are so devoted to their duty that they go with their missiles.
kanji.koohii2: Imagine those poor saps in charge of nuclear silos/ responsible for ICBMS/ those towering column missiles. When the order comes they must decide whether to obey their concience or do their duty and damn the world to atomic annihilation.

kanji.components: 心: heart; mind; spirit; heart radical (no. 61) 丿: katakana no radical (no. 4)
kanji.koohii1: You swear you´ll be in love forever/ but invariably there comes a time when your heart is divided.
kanji.koohii2: For this kanji I invariably got the stroke order wrong. I nearly lost heart/ but decided to stick (pun) to it. Then I noticed the order is 1) katakana ソ (altered slightly); 2) fishhook; 3) two drops. Now I invariably get it right.

kanji_info.image_description: A giant heart with a swirling vortex inside it, is pulling a small, helpless figure towards its center. The figure is screaming in terror, as they are sucked into the heart's depths, unable to escape the inevitable.

kanji.components: 今: now 心: heart; mind; spirit; heart radical (no. 61)
kanji.koohii1: Someone wishing from the bottom of their heart that the clock would stop. A mid-life crisis perhaps.

kanji_info.image_description: A large, clock-like heart with the word 'now' inscribed on it, is surrounded by swirling thoughts and ideas. The heart is beating wildly as it tries to keep up with the constant flow of information.

kanji.components: 自: oneself 心: heart; mind; spirit; heart radical (no. 61)

kanji_info.image_description: A giant, pulsating heart is floating in the sky, emitting a stream of breath-like bubbles. A small figure, representing a son, is sitting on one of the bubbles, looking up in awe at the heart.

short_text_with_quiz.text_japanese: 先週、のんびりとした田舎町に旅行に行きました。都会の喧騒とは全く違い、ゆっくりと過ごせました。昔の家の並ぶ静かな通りを散策したり、写真を撮ったりと、本当に気持ちの良い一日でした。地元のお店でハンバーガーを食べたのですが、値段は少し高いながらも、その美味しさに納得でした。ゆっくりと過ごせる素敵な場所でした。都会の喧騒から離れて、心身のリフレッシュをしたい方には、おすすめです。きっとあなたも、私と同じように、楽しい時間を過ごせると思います。
short_text_with_quiz.text_english: Last week, I went on a trip to a small, quiet town in the countryside. It was a nice change of pace from the bustling city. I spent the day strolling through the streets, admiring the old houses and enjoying the peace and quiet.  It was a beautiful day, and I even managed to capture some great pictures.  I ate a delicious hamburger at a local restaurant, and even though it was a bit expensive, I was willing to pay for such high quality. The town was full of charm, and it was a perfect place to relax and get away from the stress of everyday life. I definitely recommend this place for anyone looking for a peaceful and enjoyable trip. I am sure you will find it just as enjoyable as I did.
